        <num>CC 2480</num>
        <heading>2480.  Retention of possession by seller, presumption of simulation</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2480.  Retention of possession by seller, presumption of simulation
When the thing sold remains in the corporeal possession of the seller the sale is presumed to be a simulation, and, where the interest of heirs and creditors of the seller is concerned, the parties must show that their contract is not a simulation.</p>
        </content>
